{"word":"γελάω","slug":"γελάω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>γελάω</b></el> <p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><a href='S:absolute, absolutely'>absol.</a> <i>to laugh</i>, <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>; <el>ἐγέλασσεν χείλεσιν</el>, of feigned laughter, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b>:—<a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a>, <el>ἕνεκα τοῦ γελασθῆναι</el> for the sake of <i>a laugh being raised</i>, <b><a href='S:Demosthenes'>Dem.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><i>to laugh at</i> a person, <a href='S:Latin'>Lat.</a> <el>irrideo</el>, <el>ἐπί τινι</el> <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>; also at a thing, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b>; so <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:dative'>dat.</a>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>; rarely, like <el>καταγελάω</el>, <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:genitive'>gen.</a> <a href='S:person, personal'>pers.</a>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:accusative'>acc.</a> <i>to deride</i>, <el>τινά</el> or <el>τι</el> <b><a href='S:Theocritus'>Theocr.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b>:—<a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a> <i>to be derided</i>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}